underlying_goal: To commit recent work on a research paper and associated process documentation into the git repository.
primary_success: Correctly identified two logical groups of changes (paper restructuring vs. process docs) and created separate, clean commits for each.
brief_summary: The user initiated a commit. The agent analyzed the changed files, identified two distinct logical changes (paper restructuring and GDM review process documentation), and created two separate commits. It correctly excluded the compiled PDF binary and warned the user before offering to push to the main branch.
